{"key":"post-11060725","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11060725</id>\n<content>Cracker dry, then seal in vacuum bags.&amp;nbsp; I have some that have been sealed for nearly ten years now.&amp;nbsp; Every year we break out a bag and sample the contents.&amp;nbsp; They're still just as good as the day we bagged them.&amp;nbsp; Each bag gets a food-grade silica gel packet and a food-grade oxygen absorber packet.&amp;nbsp; That's the key to indefinite storage.&amp;nbsp; Ziplock bags are gas permeable so eventually the desiccant will saturate with moisture and the mushrooms will be ruined.&amp;nbsp; Vacuum bags are a total seal, as are mason jars, which also work if you'll pull a vacuum in them.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11060770</next>\n<prev>11060608</prev>\n<first>11058024</first>\n<last>11060823</last>\n<when>1252985330</when>\n<utime>09/15/09 06:28 AM</utime>\n</post>"}